<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1938,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,461,1938,1963]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Localities in the Algarve.</emphasis>
Faro (
<collectingCountry box="[544,647,1938,1963]" name="Portugal" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Portugal</collectingCountry>
), Ria 
<collectingCountry box="[722,825,1939,1962]" name="Taiwan" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Formosa</collectingCountry>
, at the entrance of the so-called Garganta channel. Higher littoral, in the outlet of a tidal pool with very coarse shell debris, mixed with coarse sand, detritus and silt (
<date box="[160,382,2010,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" value="2011-09-13">
<number box="[160,189,2011,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" value="13.0">13</number>
September 
<number box="[322,382,2011,2035]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</date>
).
</paragraph>
